article.headline: Iowa 58, W. Illinois 43
article.story: IOWA CITY, Iowa -- Jake Kelly and Jermain Davis each scored 13 points and Iowa beat Western Illinois 58-43 Saturday night for its fourth win in five games. Matt Gatens added 11 points and a career-high 10 rebounds for the Hawkeyes (10-3), who finished their non-conference schedule a perfect 8-0 at home. Iowa had trouble putting away the undersized Leathernecks, who didn't start a player taller than 6-foot-5. The Hawkeyes trailed by one at halftime and needed a 9-1 run midway in the second half to get some breathing room. The Leathernecks got as close as 36-35 before Iowa held them scoreless for a 4 1/2-minute stretch. Devan Bawinkel's 3 put the Hawkeyes up 45-36 with 6:29 left, and Davis's dunk made it 53-43 with 2:02 to go. David DuBois had 18 points to lead Western Illinois (4-8), which lost its third straight and fell to 0-8 against Iowa. The Hawkeyes open Big Ten play at Ohio State on Dec. 31.
